// PEOPLE FAQ
OnWhoFirsts : all
{
	articleopencount++
	
	"\0\s[0]\t\*\b2"
	--
	"Ah! The First Aces... \s[1]as you can most likely extrapolate from the title, these were the, ehm, first-ever Ace Cards. \s[0]An Ace, as you may already know, is a Card with an entirely different type of flow than ordinary folks like you and I. The Firsts, however, were a whole other story... they appeared during a time of great unrest, starting one thousand and thirty-seven years ago, in an event we now call The Emergence. \n\s[1]First to emerge was Viro, First Ace of Spades; a tall man with thickly curled horns and salt-and-pepper hair, he appeared from the mist, walking out of a thick forest of Velanne covered in dirt and his own blood. He disappeared as quickly as he was found.\n A few months later, something similar happened in Lacerta -- \s[0]Lairu of Hearts was found unconscious in the middle of the desert, and brought to a small village near modern-day Chiluno. When they awoke, they spoke in tongues no one had ever heard of -- or heard since. \s[3]Though they seemed to have sustained injuries to vital organs, and no Parasite was seemingly present in their body to regulate their energyflow, they got off of the doctor's operation table and walked straight into a blustering sandstorm, not to be seen again for months.\n \s[0]Nore of Clubs walked out of the ocean covered in seafoam, marching straight through villages and towns until they arrived in the heart of Thiremor. There, they sat down, crossed their legs, closed their eyes, and sank into the earth, with no sign they'd ever been there at all. Witnesses wrote that the patch of earth they'd disappeared into later grew strange plants, ones that weren't normally native to Aidhmoore. "
	
		"\w9\w9\n\n\f[color,disable]\f[sup,1]\![quicksection,1]click anywhere to continue\n\q[click here to quit reading the article,OnBACK]\![quicksection,0]\f[sup,0]\f[color,default]\x \s[0]\b[2]"
	
	"\s[1]Of course, all of these happenings were seen as these scary, horrible omens -- which, in hindsight, makes a lot of sense...\n \s[0]Lairu was the first to reappear, not seeming to remember being found near-dead in the desert just a year prior -- they showcased immense magical talent, however, and became a sort of shepherd of the then-suffering suit of Hearts.\n Viro reappeared next, his memories of the bizarre event also faded. Attempting to enter society, he challenged the people of Paccevela to lighthearted duels and quickly earned the title of 'the Bloodied Gladiator' -- the, er, 'Bloodied' part being in reference to his omen-like appearance from the year before. The duels themselves were never to the death, only until someone \f[height,-2]-- or, well, only ever Viro's opponent --\f[height,default] tapped out. He later wrote that he never liked that title, but that 'as long as my people are happy, I am happy.' \s[1]How nice of him..!\n\n \s[0]Nore appeared right where they had sank into the earth a year before, keeping somewhat away from society. People who met them wrote that they had a deeply anxious soul. "
	
		"\w9\w9\n\n\f[color,disable]\f[sup,1]\![quicksection,1]click anywhere to continue\n\q[click here to quit reading the article,OnBACK]\![quicksection,0]\f[sup,0]\f[color,default]\x \s[0]\b[2]"
	
	
	"Eventually, Lairu and Nore met, when the former was scoping for new territory to move into -- \s[3]the Hearts were wanting desperately to escape Lacerta, after making the already-unstable area now known as the Black Desert even worse... \s[1]ehm, more on that \_a[OnWhoAlonaia]some other time, when I talk about Alonai'a\_a, though. \s[0]Nore seemed calmed by the other's presence, and from then on they were inseperable. \s[3]Not exactly a \f[italic,1]healthy\f[italic,default] relationship, but it was definitely something.\n\n \s[1]Lairu decided they'd attempt to take over the last remaining quadrant -- Kosanu. Nore stayed behind; they and Viro had started to get along quite well, and Viro didn't agree with trying to take over Kosanu.\n \s[0]Lairu's plans, er, didn't go well... \s[1]but since I don't wish to talk your ear off, \_a[OnWhoAlonaia]I'll let you choose if you want me to continue, haha!\_a\w3 It's up to you, if you're up to hearing the rest."
	
		"\w9\w9\n\n\f[color,disable]\f[sup,1]\![quicksection,1]click anywhere to continue\n\q[click here to quit reading the article,OnBACK]\![quicksection,0]\f[sup,0]\f[color,default]\x \s[0]\b[2]"
	
	
	"After the whole debacle with Lairu in Kosanu, \_a[OnWhoAlonaia]and the emergence of Alonai'a\_a, as well as the... \s[3]\w9subsequent events\w2 surrounding her and the other Firsts,\w2\s[1] it's said their souls entered a sort of in-between state -- the Aces born after them had not the souls of the Firsts, \s[0]but simply a blessing set upon them to grant them that same flow. Instead, their spirits are said to reside mostly over their own Quadrants -- sometimes visiting their shrines, or places they had been during their lives.\n\n \s[3]...It's been twenty-three years since I last felt her presence in the temple. I count the days. She sent me a sign, an amicable omen wrapped in the smoke of incense, and then she was gone. Perhaps... \f[height,-2]mm, \f[italic,1]no,\f[italic,default]\w3 I mustn't drag you into my baseless theories. \_a[OnWhoGuardians]Gio\_a is right; even if I'm correct, I shouldn't be telling folks all about it... it might get people feeling restless.\f[height,default]\n \w9...\s[0]Ehm, my apologies. I get carried away when I think of the final sign she sent me -- \s[1]\w2perhaps I'm just getting too old, losing my marbles and such. \n...Hopefully this answer suffices, for now. \s[0]Even if not, don't worry... it's hard to keep me from bringing up the Firsts for long!..\n \s[1]Thank you for letting me ramble. Oh, and... if you're ready for \_a[OnWhoAlonaia]the second half of the story\_a, do let me know!.."

	--
	"\n\n\n\![*]\q[Back to dictionary,OnBACK]\n\![*]\q[Thank you,Cancel]\n"

