OnWhoAlonaia : all // ........jesus fucking christ this is so long
{
	articleopencount++
	if Flag("kyone mentioned") == 0; MiscFlags ,= "kyone mentioned"
	
	"\0\s[0]\t\*\b2"
	--
	"You wish to know of Alonai'a, %(oomf)? Well, \s[1]you certainly have come to the right place, ha! \s[0]Let's see, how do I capture her essence in its entirety... aha, of course!..\w9\w9\s[1]I shall start from the beginning.\n\n "
	"\s[0]Alonai'a was born from nothing; she emerged from the dusty snow of Kosanu \f[height,-2]-- in the region now known as Ani'ana Prefecture --\f[height,default] fully fledged, with an energetic flow the likes of which, atleast for us Diamonds, had never been read before. Alonai'a was -- or, rather, is -- the First Ace of Diamonds.\n\n "
	"Before her, our Suit struggled to survive; the harsh conditions of Kosanu were bad enough, but we had recently been ravaged by war -- the Hearts, desperate to escape the Black Desert...\w8\f[height,-2]er,\w4 more on that later,\w8\f[height,default] plundered countless Diamond villages, wreaking destruction and shedding the deep cerulean blood of our kind as they advanced onward. This event came to be known as the Snowblind Massacre, as the Hearts army would wait for snowstorms to attack, \s[3]taking out villages covertly as they were obscured by the harsh weather...\n\n "
	
		"\w9\w9\n\n\f[color,disable]\f[sup,1]\![quicksection,1]click anywhere to continue\n\q[click here to quit reading the article,OnBACK]\![quicksection,0]\f[sup,0]\f[color,default]\x \s[0]\b[2]"
	
	"\w5\s[1]We do not know who or what created Alonai'a. She did not know, herself. But she knew that this massacre, pointless and cruel, needed to be put to an end.\n \s[0]As the army of Hearts advanced north, closer to Alonai'a's place of emergence, the freshly formed Ace froze them in their tracks. A vortex of energy emerged, invisible to the naked eye -- titled by researchers later on as an \f[italic,1]'Imaginary Sinkhole'\f[italic,default]. The army dropped dead; hundreds of lives taken in an instant, their blood drained straight from their bodies and their energy alongside it. Behind them, stretching for miles, the then-pale blue snow was bleached a sickening, blinding bone-white. The effect of the Imaginary Sinkhole carried through the air, and a faint, shrill screech could be heard alongside it. \s[3]The \_a[OnKyone]Kyone Tundra\_a had been born.\n\n "
	"\w9\s[1]This was an act done by Alonai'a not only to save her people from certain death, but also to bring balance to the land. See, she was the last Ace to awaken, and Lairu -- First Ace of Hearts -- had recently created a stark imbalance in the land itself; \s[0]they, using their own Imaginary Sinkhole, had sewn the seeds of the Black Desert.\n\w9\w8The Black Desert, with its extensive energy spikes, had been the thing to drive the Hearts out of their territory in the first place... the Kyone, opposite of the Desert in every way, put each Suit back into its sacred home.\s[0]"
	
		"\w9\w9\n\n\f[color,disable]\f[sup,1]\![quicksection,1]click anywhere to continue\n\q[click here to quit reading the article,OnBACK]\![quicksection,0]\f[sup,0]\f[color,default]\x\b[2]"
	
	"\s[1]This was, to put it lightly, quite the eventful awakening. \s[0]After the creation of the \_a[OnKyone]Kyone\_a, as well as the end of the Snowblind Massacre, Alonai'a was able to settle down and figure out how to truly live. She documented much of her life in thick diaries -- \s[1]which I, of course, have read cover-to-cover more times than I can count...\w9 er, anyways!..\s[0]\n She started travelling to places near and far, documenting her experiences as she went. She wrote much of the beautiful sights she beheld, the exquisite cuisines she sampled, people she met... they are a wonderful read. I recommend them, if ever you have the time.\n\n "
	"\w9In these books, she also details bits and pieces of her relationship with Viro, the First Ace of Spades. The young couple went everywhere together, absolutely inseparable...\s[1] so cute, hehe. They were going to get married, before...\w9\s[3] well.\n\n "
	"\w9\w6\s[3]...The freshly budding monarchy didn't take kindly to the Aces' display of power; they especially disliked Lairu and Alonai'a's ability to create energetic anomalies at will, parts of the landmass that were now entirely uninhabitable -- \s[0]or, rather, unconquerable.\n \s[3]The Facecards formed two elite squadrons of high-level Jacks, and sent both of them out at roughly the same time to find Lairu and Alonai'a. "
	
		"\w9\w9\n\n\f[color,disable]\f[sup,1]\![quicksection,1]click anywhere to continue\n\q[click here to quit reading the article,OnBACK]\![quicksection,0]\f[sup,0]\f[color,default]\x \s[0]\b[2]"
	
	"Lairu was an easy target; they had grown arrogant after they created the Desert, parading themselves around as if there were no metaphorical target on their back... easy pickings. The First Ace of Hearts had been slain.\n\n "
	"\s[1]Alonai'a, on the other hand, was not so easy to take down. \s[0]As she travelled alongside Viro, she had an added layer of protection; the Facecards knew this, and they prepared much more thoroughly than with Lairu.\n The following is knowledge from Viro's account of events...\n\n "
	"After catching wind of the assassination plot -- as well as the death of Lairu, Viro convinced Alonai'a to stay behind and hide, as she had recently sustained an injury that would make fighting much more difficult. She reluctantly agreed, locking herself in the small cottage where they had been staying during their travels.\n \s[1]When the squadron arrived, Viro took them down with ease...\w9\w1 \s[3]or so he thought.\w8 The first wave of attackers was a ruse, a distraction to lure Viro away from his beloved. \w9When he got back to the cottage, the door was open, a trail of deep blue blood mixing with dark maroon.\n\n "
	"Inside, Alonai'a lay dying, the corpses of dozens of assassins around her. She had put up a fight, but ultimately, they had taken the injured Ace of Diamonds by surprise.\n Viro tried in vain to save her, revive her, anything. But though he was the First Ace, he was no god. As she slowly faded away, she told him that they wouldn't be apart long. Viro wrote her final words in his own memoirs;\w7 \n\n"
	"		\s[0]\f[italic,1]'Though the stars may keep us apart, I will find you, my love, \s[1]and together we will finish what we started.'\f[italic,default]"
	
		"\w9\w9\n\n\f[color,disable]\f[sup,1]\![quicksection,1]click anywhere to continue\n\q[click here to quit reading the article,OnBACK]\![quicksection,0]\f[sup,0]\f[color,default]\x\b[2]"
	
	"\s[3]Viro was inconsolable. He besieged the main outpost of the Facecards, taking in one fell swoop somewhere around three thousand lives. Among them was the Third Madame, Marijha Ilarus -- the woman who organized the squadron to assassinate his beloved.\n He carried out three more heavy attacks on Facecard fortresses... and then, he disappeared.\n\n "
	"For two years, he wandered Paccevela -- what was supposed to be his homeland. He wrote that he didn't belong, that the same people he was trying to protect had now turned against him; Facecard propaganda had made the Pip population believe that the Aces were villains, here to disrupt the 'natural order' -- these Pips formed a Facecard-run military.\n The last thing he wanted was for these people -- \f[italic,1]his\f[italic,default] people -- to fall under a monarchical tyranny, run by murderers. Alas, it was too late; the story was printed, his face on every 'Wanted' poster in the four Quadrants.\n\n "
	"He planned -- and swiftly carried out -- a final act. He marched into Iy Palacca, appearing to surrender himself. \s[1]That prince, ha. He is only remembered as the Son of Ilarus; too insignificant of a figure to put a name to. The poor bastard was so full of himself, he didn't think to restrain the Ace as Viro walked into his halls. Beheaded, dead in an instant. Viro only smiled as the royal blood seeped through the carpet.\n\n "
	"\s[3]From here, he was done. He laid prone on his stomach, instructing the guards\w4 -- \s[1]\f[height,-2]useless as they were, couldn't even stop a second regicide\f[height,default]\s[0] -- to pierce his energetic hotspot: the giant Spade symbol on his back. \s[3]I will...\w9 spare you\w5 the details...\n\n "
	"\_w[2000]\s[1]Ah, Viro. He went out on his own terms.\n Though he wasn't yet returned to the arms of his lover in the stars,\w6 I have a sneaking suspicion that their souls have recently taken root in new vessels. \s[3]Alonai'a's final wish may finally be coming true.\w3\n\n I hope so... they both deserve a happy ending.\w9\w9"
	--
	"\n\n\n\![*]\q[Back to dictionary,OnBACK]\n\![*]\q[Thank you,Cancel]\n"
	
	if Flag("viro") == 0; MiscFlags ,= "viro"
	if Flag("alonai'a") == 0; MiscFlags ,= "alonai'a"
	
	if Flag("lairu") == 1 && Flag("nore") == 1
	{ if Flag("firsts") == 0; MiscFlags ,= "firsts" }
}

OnWhoMadame : all // i loved writing this because they just. hate her So fucking much LMFAOOOO
{
	articleopencount++
	
	"\0\s[0]\b2\t\*"
	--
	"Oh,\w3 I see... you wish to know more about Madame Ymu. Well, you have probably gathered that she is the ruler of this land...\w7 the Queen of Clubs, Madame Siersha, handed down the crown to her at the turn of the century. This took place 37 years ago now, making Madame Ymu the Queen of Hearts...\w9\w9\w9 haha, yes, I know. The cycle can be a bit confusing... "
		
		//"\_a[OnWhatMonarchCycle]I can explain that in more detail later,\_a if you need.\n\n "
		"all you need to know is that the crown changes hands between Suits at about the start of every century, or when the current Madame steps down. Anyway, back to Ymu...\n\n "
	
	"Just like all the Madames before her, \s[3]she is a tyrant. Time and time again, she does things that put the entire lower and middle classes in complete jeopardy: raising taxes for seemingly no reason, passing laws that benefit only herself...\n \s[1]We Pips tend to dislike her -- and all her rich little friends -- but we can't exactly do much about it.\n\n "
	"\w9\s[0]Being the Shrine Guardian of Kosanu, I am forced --\w9 or, to put it in her terms, \w3\f[italic,1]strongly\w3 invited\f[italic,default]\w3 to attend gatherings of hers at Iy Pallaca.\n These are usually grand feasts, except, \w9of course,\w9 only Jacks and Facecards are ever allowed to dine on the actual main course...\w9\w9 I always sneak a few bites, but don't tell anyone.\n \w9Oh, right... the events are held to...\w7 er...\w9 well, they're \f[italic,1]supposed\f[italic,default] to be something along the lines of a voting process, asking all the officials what laws they'd like to see passed, et cetera... but she's\w3 a bit of a drunk,\w4 so...\w6 it always just devolves into a party. "
	
		"\w9\w9\n\n\f[color,disable]\f[sup,1]\![quicksection,1]click anywhere to continue\n\q[click here to quit reading the article,OnBACK]\![quicksection,0]\f[sup,0]\f[color,default]\x \s[0]\b[2]"
	
	"\w9Occasionally, she will try to push for us Guardians to sign over the rights to the shrines. The shrines are, and always will be, pieces of 'Reserved' property:\w8 this means that they are not under the jurisdiction of the monarchy, and the Queen may not alter, create, or destroy the laws surrounding them. These temples are the last things she cannot touch.\n \w8We all say no, of course. She is not good at hiding her fury; every time we refuse, that long, unsightly face of hers turns bright red, her eyes all but popping out of her head...\w9 it's my favourite source of entertainment, if I'm honest with you.\n\n "
	"\w9Her nephew, Vol, is all but confirmed to the public as the Ace of Hearts. She parades him around like a trophy, and he loves it. He gets all the attention he could ever want.\n My good friend Inola, who is the Shrine Guardian of Lacerta, is embarrassed to be represented by him...\w9 I can't blame her, ha! I would be too.\w9\w6 He's the definition of \f[italic,1]'overgrown brat.'\f[italic,default]\n\n "
	"\w9Ooh, right... since I'm forced to deal with her so often, I've at least picked up some fun facts... ehehe.\n She's had her fair share of assassination attempts. She cries on and on about them at the yearly gatherings; looking around the table, you can tell which people are wishing the attempts went through...\n What else, what else... ah, yes. There was one time I remember where she simply couldn't hold her liquor, and passed out on the floor of her own palace, facefirst into her own... er, we'll just say \f[italic,1]dinner\f[italic,default]. Truly, an embarrassing woman --\w9\w9 but I suppose those with enough money and power need not true dignity, right? Ha...\w9\w9\s[1] pure insanity.\n\n "
	"\w9\w5\s[0]I think that's all I've got... I try not to pay her much mind. I am lucky I have the ability to tune her out... I can simply work on my writing while she prattles away in the background.\n\n "
	"\w9\w9Hopefully, this answer suffices...\s[1]\w9 I apologize for cutting off the explanation here, but I'm afraid I simply cannot talk about her much more without getting nauseous. \s[0]If there's anything more pleasant you'd like to pivot to, please do let me know... \w9\s[1]ehehe."
	--
	"\n\n\n\![*]\q[Back to dictionary,OnBACK]\n\![*]\q[Thank you,Cancel]\n"
	
	if Flag("madame") == 0; MiscFlags ,= "madame"
	if Flag("inola") == 0; MiscFlags ,= "inola"
	if Flag("vol") == 0; MiscFlags ,= "vol"
}


OnWhoDel : all
{
	articleopencount++
	
	"\0\s[0]\t\*\b2"
	--
	"Ah, that Del. \s[1]Ha...colourful fellow. \s[0]Not much is known about the current Aces, as they aren't to be officially revealed for another decade. \s[1]But... as the shrine guardian, I get to bear witness to a bit more information than the general public.\n \s[0]Anyways... Del Noccione is the Ace of Spades. He was born to Elina and Rollas Noccione, two \_a[OnWhatFlow]Jacks\_a who were very well-respected in \_a[OnScavva]Scavva\_a. Rollas also happened to be a member of the royal guard.\n ...His mother, Elina, was a Seer -- she knew that her son was an Ace from the moment he was born. However, she knew what that meant; \s[1]Aces... do not get to stay with their family. \s[3]They are forced to enroll in The Academy as young as possible, and their parents do not get to see them until well into their teenagehood -- or, worse, even later into adulthood. \s[1]She, who had had extreme troubles with her pregnancy, could not safely have another child. \s[0]So, she did what any mother would do; \s[3]she cloaked her baby's energy with a spell...\n \s[0]When the Royal Seers came to examine him, they were shocked -- high flow, which both Elina and Rollas had, is usually genetic... \s[3]\w9\w9but Del was coming up with no flow at all. He was labelled a \f[italic,1]'zero.'\f[italic,default]\n\n \s[1]"
	"His father, who had no clue Elina had done any of this, was furious. His only son, the only continuation of his bloodline, flowless -- in his eyes, \s[3]useless. He mistreated his son... and eventually, when his anger and hatred spread, he started to mistreat Elina as well. Elina's lie may have kept her son safe from the prying hands of the Facecards, but it could not protect either of them from the hands and harsh words of his father. "
	
		"\w9\w9\n\n\f[color,disable]\f[sup,1]\![quicksection,1]click anywhere to continue\n\q[click here to quit reading the article,OnBACK]\![quicksection,0]\f[sup,0]\f[color,default]\x \s[0]\b[2]"
	
	"When he turned eleven years old, his mother told him the truth. For his entire life up to that point, he hadn't even tried to learn magic -- why would he? No flow to control. \s[1]Ha... little did he know, he had more power than most of us could ever dream of.\n \s[0]In secret, she began to teach him to control his magic. And oh, he was a \f[italic,1]natural.\f[italic,default] I myself have seen him spar, while visiting Iy Palacca -- he took down that Ace of Hearts, with all his royal blood and big ego, without even breaking a sweat! A sore loser, that Vol. Oh, right, back to the story...\n\n "
	"He managed to evade being found as the Ace of Spades until he was fourteen, before he got into a fight with some guard who was on the same squadron as his father... the man had insulted Elina. Del got overzealous, used some high-level spell and exposed himself as, well, anything \f[italic,1]but\f[italic,0] a 'zero.' His mother, the poor woman... her own husband brought her to the Palace, where she was \f[height,-2]\w9allegedly\w9\f[height,default] executed for treason against the Madame. After Viro, First Ace of Spades, killed two monarchs in a row all those centuries ago, well... keeping an Ace hidden from the Facecards became one of the worst crimes you could ever commit, no matter your reasons.\n\n "
	"And so, a teenage Del was ripped away from his mother and forcibly enrolled in The Academy. He was so young, then. \n \s[3]\w9\w9...He's young, still.\n \s[0]\w9\w9I've got no idea how he wasn't read as an Ace the instant they got their hands on him, spell or no spell. \s[0]He simply bursts with this... \s[1]\f[italic,1]spark.\f[italic,default] When he walks into a room, it's just this\w3 overwhelming,\w3 potent energy. \s[0]My few conversations with him left me wanting to pick his brain more and more. \n\s[3]\w9...For someone so young, it feels as if he has lived a thousand years.\n\n \w9\w9"
	
	"\s[1]...About a year ago, he disappeared... \w9along with the freshly found Ace of Diamonds, \_a[OnWhoAllo]Allo Ukagi.\_a Madame Ymu is... not happy about it. The Facecards have been trying to discreetly find and imprison him, all while not causing a public panic. It's... not going well for them. On top of being a great fighter, Del has learned to keep secrets -- and keep them \f[italic,1]well\f[italic,default] -- all his life. \s[0]I am confident that they will not find him. I certainly don't want them to... \s[3]I believe he has a far more important role in this world than to simply become another pawn.\n \w9\w9\s[1]...Perhaps, in time, he will finish what his long-passed predecessor started."
	
	--
	"\n\n\n\![*]\q[Back to dictionary,OnBACK]\n\![*]\q[Thank you,Cancel]\n"
	
	if Flag("del") == 0; MiscFlags ,= "del"
	if Flag("allo article") == 0; MiscFlags ,= "allo article"
}

OnWhoAllo : all
{
	articleopencount++
	"\0\s[0]\t\*\b2"
	--
	"\0\s[3]...The Ace of Diamonds, Allo Ukagi. \w9I wish I knew more, %(oomf). \s[0]I have only been in his presence once. \s[3]All I know is that he is young, and kind, and very deeply in love.\n\n "
	"\s[1]\w9\w9...Alright, so perhaps I do know a bit more. \s[0]However, most of it is hearsay, whispered amongst the guards and staff at Iy Palacca... \w9\w9\s[3]as well as information from journals that he left at The Academy when he and \_a[OnWhoDel]Del\_a disappeared.\n \w9They were delivered to me to translate, as they were in our shared native language, and I am the only Ani'ani to Common translator that they know.\n \s[1]\f[italic,1]...Of course,\f[italic,default] as an act of gentle rebellion against Ymu, I sent her back a false translation, and kept the journals for safekeeping... \s[3]as well as for research, comparison with\w2.\w2.\w2.\w9 another certain set of journals. There is more to this era's Aces than meets the eye, I am sure of it. \n \w9\s[1]...It's not as if Ymu will ever be able to tell the difference; of course, nobody in her lineup of cronies is Kosani, and they will never see the original journals again. They need not pry into the brain of the young boy who they kidnapped for their own gain, anyway. \n...\w9\s[3]I feel guilty reading them, as well. However... the way that they are written indicates that he knew this would happen anyway, and even wanted it to. \s[0]In other words, they are written \f[italic,1]to\f[italic,default] the reader. Interestingly, in he and I's native language, the journals use a set of second-person pronouns dedicated solely to addressing someone with power over the author. Upon my initial read-through, I wondered if they were perhaps written to Ymu, or even to the other Aces, but... upon further reading, it outright states that they addressed to 'the Firsts\w9\w9\w9 \f[italic,1]and\w9 their Guardians\f[italic,default].' \w9\s[1]As you can imagine, I was very surprised to have been mentioned! I did not think he remembered me. "
	
		"\w9\w9\n\n\f[color,disable]\f[sup,1]\![quicksection,1]click anywhere to continue\n\q[click here to quit reading the article,OnBACK]\![quicksection,0]\f[sup,0]\f[color,default]\x \s[0]\b[2]"
	
	"\w9\w9\s[3]Ah... right. \n...As I mentioned, I have met him once. Unlike what you may assume, we did not meet at the Palace, where I met some of the others. We did not even meet "
	{
		if locslot == "shrine";	"here, at this shrine."
		else; "at the Kosani Shrine of Aces."
	}
	" No... \s[0]we met years ago, when he was just a child.\n \s[1]I was visiting the temple I used to train in, on the main island of Ani'ana. It was a holy day, and as Guardian, I occasionally like to see how the smaller shrines are doing, help them along... this time was different, though. \s[3]Something was calling to me.\n\n "
	"Something about the Shrines is that, on holy days, their doors have an energetic lock on them that only a shrine's attendant or Guardian, as well as -- of course -- any Ace, can undo. It was put in place by the first Guardians to keep negative energy from breaching the temples... a simple mechanism, really.\n ...I was helping an old pupil of mine settle into their new role as the attendant, telling her about my time there... when we heard the door unlock. Very strange, as we hadn't invited the other students to help. When we looked back into the main hall, a small child was looking up at a painting of the Firsts of Diamonds and Spades together,\w9 and crying.\n We tried to ask the little child where his parents were, how he got in... but the child simply looked back at the door and left. As he turned to leave the temple, I noticed a brightly shining Stigma of Diamonds on the back of his neck.\n \w8I tried to follow the child outside, but he was gone. A cold wind blew bright, shining fog across the landscape, covering the child's tracks. I realized that this was the one and only time I would be in the presence of the Ace of Diamonds for a very, very long time. "
	
		"\w9\w9\n\n\f[color,disable]\f[sup,1]\![quicksection,1]click anywhere to continue\n\q[click here to quit reading the article,OnBACK]\![quicksection,0]\f[sup,0]\f[color,default]\x \s[0]\b[2]"
	
	"I trust that he is safe, alongside the Ace of Spades. I felt so silly reading these parts of his journals... \s[1]until I remembered he practically addressed them to me, that is... \s[1]but he waxed poetic on and on about how safe Del always made him feel, as well as -- hehe, it cracks me up just thinking about it... he always doodled Del's face in the margins of the paper, talked about how pretty he was. It's all so very sweet... \s[3]and, it's a nice break from reading about the downright torture that Ymu put him through to find his powers.\n\n ...He wrote about how, as a child, after his parents all but left him to die in the bone-chilling wilderness of the island Inei, he wandered for years and years, sometimes going weeks without food. All he had to comfort him was the pale warmth emanating from his neck\w9 -- \s[1]perhaps he still doesn't know quite what that was, but... the energetic hotspots, or \w2\f[italic,1]stigmata\f[italic,default]\w2 of an Ace are the greatest sources of their energy. \s[3]The warmth he felt emanating from the double-Diamond stigmata on his neck was\w3... likely the last of his energetic reserves, working overtime to keep him from dropping dead.\n He wrote that he would pass through towns, sleep in abandoned sheds or behind restaurants, surviving by sneaking into the kitchens of those closed restaurants at night to 'borrow' -- \s[1]as he puts it -- \s[3]their soon-to-expire foods. On occasion, he would hang around the windows of schools, listening in on the lessons to try to scrap together an education of some kind. Despite his knowledge of being an Ace, he barely knew anything about what that meant -- other than the fact that he should have magic, and somehow... didn't. Up to the last pages, he writes that he still has no idea what his powers are, how he is even an Ace... hence the abuse from the higher-ups at the Academy.\n "
	"He also writes that he... avoided the temples on purpose, though he knew they'd have to take him in, because... the last thing his mother had said to him before \f[italic,1]leaving him\f[italic,default] to \f[italic,1]rot\f[italic,default] was that...\w9\w9 he was the Ace of Diamonds.\n\n As I got to the journal titled 'ninth' -- \s[1]that's right, this was nine journals' worth, and he had only started them a few months before disappearing!.. The tone started to shift. \s[3]As opposed to that comparatively vague 'written to the Firsts and their Guardians' note, \s[1]the ninth journal consisted solely of a sort of 'letter' addressed to... \s[3]ehm, \w6\f[italic,1]me\f[italic,default]. \w8He writes that, as a child with very little knowledge of how the temples worked, he had assumed that I, or any of the shrine attendants, would be obligated to bring him to the Madame -- something he later learned was the opposite of true -- and so he avoided us. He then writes that he had come to regret it, that he had heard great things about me from Del -- \s[1]he always did know how to flatter me, that young man -- \s[0]and that, if he could change one thing... \w9the first thing that he would have done\s[3]\w9... would be to come to me, \w5tell me everything that had happened, and gone with whatever I decided was best. That... was the last 'chapter' in the final journal, before the pages run blank, the rest of the story following a paperless trail alongside his beloved. Every time I read it, it sends an ache to the pit of my heart, one that I had forgotten I could feel. I hope he knows, now, that I would never have done a single thing to cause him harm.\n\n ...\w9\s[1]Thank you. It was... \w9it was good to tell someone. You are... a good listener, %(oomf).\n \w9\s[3]..."
	
	--
	"\n\n\n\![*]\q[Back to dictionary,OnBACK]\n\![*]\q[Thank you,Cancel]\n"
	
	if Flag("allo") == 0; MiscFlags ,= "allo"
}


