OnAnianaprefecture : all
{	
	articleopencount++
	
	"\0\s[0]\t\*"
	--
	"Ah! Ani'ana Prefecture, my homeland... of course I'll tell you about it! Let's see, where should we start?..\n Ani'ana Prefecture is a large group of many small islands on the north and west coasts of Kosanu. The Prefecture gets its name from the largest island of them, named simply Ani'ana... \s[1]this naming convention tends to confuse foreigners, so don't feel too bad if you're not following, ehehe.\s[0]\n "
	"This island is where Alonai'a emerged -- which is why their names sound somewhat similar... there are many small temples dedicated to her there, including the shrine I trained and took my ceremonial tests at, many years ago. Oh, ehm, fun fact! That shrine is actually older than any other on the continent; it was built before Alonai'a even emerged, constructed about 1,200 years ago, in hopes that a savior would come... \s[1]I suppose, one truly did! Anyways... the surrounding islands are much smaller, really only having two or three villages each to their name...\s[0]\n "
	"The western islands extend down, peppering themselves into Aidhish territory; Oltronnt, a large island sitting snugly between the territorial lines, derives its name from the Aidhish term 'shared space,' and is home to a half-and-half population of the two Suits. For tax reasons, however, the entire island is considered to be included in Ani'ana Prefecture... \s[1]oh, that was a tangent, wasn't it? Ehehe... right, back on track.\n\n "

	"The history of the region is vast, as the islands were basically the Diamond's only home for several thousand years. Until we figured out seafaring, we lived in the vast caves of Ani'ana, coming out at night to fish and play in the snow...\n" 
	"A few millennia into our civilization, we finally figured out boats. It's not as easy as you'd think; we didn't exactly work with wood very often, nor did we have a wealth of trees to experiment with in the first place!.. Anyway, some of us sailed to what is now \_a[OnShuioNui]Shui'o Nui\_a, and some of us stayed in Ani'ana. Our civilizations were growing wonderfully, enough to split into two groups!.. Those who travelled to Shui'o Nui incorporated a mail system, to keep communication between the two settlements quick and easy... \s[1]very efficient! \n\n"

	"\w9\w9...On a more modern note, the cuisine in Ani'ana is vastly different than that of Shui'o Nui.. As it is an island, we of course eat lots of fish... \s[1]well, alright. I admit, we eat lots of fish here in Shui'o Nui, but...\w9 but it's different! \s[3]Ehm...\n \s[0]Ani'ani cuisine focuses more on utilizing offshore crops, such as oceangrass. My favourite dish from the island is Saltscale Grassrolls... it's raw or smoked Saltscale, wrapped in oceangrass and frozen! Very good...\w9 er, where was I? Right! Ehm...\n\n "

	"It's smart to have knowledge of seafaring before you try to make your way out to the islands. The water gets very choppy on the north side, due in part to bordering the Kyone... I'd recommend getting a few sailing lessons before you visit."
	--
	"\n\n\n\![*]\q[More about Kosanu,OnKosanuBACK]\n\![*]\q[Back to dictionary,OnBACK]\n\![*]\q[Thank you,Cancel]\n"
	
	if Flag("underground") == 0; MiscFlags ,= "underground"
}

OnShuioNui : all
{
	articleopencount++
	
	"\0\s[0]\t\*"
	--
	"Shui'o Nui Prefecture is the mainland section of Kosanu. We're in eastern Shui'o Nui right now, in fact!\n"
	"This was the second main home of our kind, the first being \_a[OnAnianaprefecture]Ani'ana Prefecture\_a. The travellers who first came to Shui'o Nui were excited to see that the caves here were much larger, and would be able to house our ever-growing population much more comfortably... \s[1]little did we know, a few hundred years into our inhabitance there, the earthquakes would come and destroy most of those cave dwellings. \s[0]This forced our kind to the surface, which, while challenging to get used to at first, \s[1]\w2proved to actually be quite great! \w3\s[0]Farming was made a bit easier, our eyes became less sensitive to light as time went on, and -- get this -- \s[1]we started actually meeting folks from the other Quadrants! \s[0]We hadn't even known we weren't alone on this big hunk of rock before that..! As the earthquakes continued, we decided we'd just relocate our civilization to the surface... and the rest is history. "
	
	"\n\n\s[1]\w9.\w2.\w2.\w2Oh dear. I went on a big old ramble there, now, didn't I?.. Hum. I suppose I should tell you about \f[italic,1]modern\f[italic,default] Shui'o Nui, hm?.. Hehe!\n \s[0]"
	"Shui'o Nui is so large that it spans quite a few climates, but, ehm... \s[1]\w4it's all quite cold. \w8\s[0]I mean, not to \f[italic,1]me,\f[italic,default]\w3 but I can definitely see why we don't get many visitors -- \s[1]other than ones who are here to hog our hotsprings.\n \s[0]In Western Shui'o Nui, where the land borders the West Ocean, we have luscious evergreen forests, with aromatic Eke trees and thousands of wild Kikuminu... over here in Eastern Shui'o Nui, however, it is much more barren. The area directly bordering \_a[OnScavva]Scavva\_a, separated by the large Northern Quatangu Canal, has some spotty forests here and there, but... ehm, \s[1]lumber isn't exactly our main export, if you understand what I mean. \s[0]That's why it's so sparsely populated, as well... harder to find materials to build the houses, ehe.\n\n "
	
	"\s[1]The main cuisine of Shui'o Nui isn't much different than that of Ani'ana Prefecture; fish! \s[0]As far inland as we are, you tend to find a more roots-and-noodles based menu at restaurants and such, \s[1]but there's still quite a bit of seafood if you know where to look. \s[0]My favourite thing here that we never grew back on the islands is this root called wedgeflower; when it's ripe enough to pluck from the earth, it sprouts up from the snow with these cute little purple flowers \s[1]-- wedge shaped, if you can quite believe it -- \w2\s[0]and it tastes just \f[italic,1]so\f[italic,default] nice in a warm fish and noodle dish. \s[1]Really, any dish will do! It's quite versatile... \s[0]I always add a little to my stew, it really brings out the creaminess... \w6\s[1]ehm! But anyway! I'll quit talking your ear off about food. \s[0]I hope I answered all your questions about the Prefecture! \s[1]If you'd like to know about anywhere else, just ask away."
	--
	"\n\n\n\![*]\q[More about Kosanu,OnKosanuBACK]\n\![*]\q[Back to dictionary,OnBACK]\n\![*]\q[Thank you,Cancel]\n"
}

OnKyone : all
{
	articleopencount++
	"\0\s[3]\t\*"
	--
	"Mmm. Well, \w9\s[1]I suppose it's hard not to ask about the giant energetic anomaly stretching across the entire northeastern side of our Quadrant, isn't it?.. Alright. I'll tell you about the Kyone.\n\n \s[0]As you know, \_a[OnWhoAlonaia]Alonai'a\_a created the Tundra to stop the Hearts from infringing on the sacred land of the Diamonds... but, ehm, \s[1]\w4she later realized that she could not reverse it. \s[0]Both the Black Desert and the Kyone Tundra were outside the realm of things even the Firsts were capable of changing.\n She wasn't very happy about this, as you can imagine; she wanted her people to be safe anywhere in Kosanu, and she felt responsible for the newfound danger of the area... she worked hard to try to find a way to reverse her actions, but unfortunately, \s[1]being chased around by the Facecards all the time didn't lend much time to research.\n\n "
	
	"\s[3]\w9...After her untimely demise, we simply decided it was best to leave the Kyone alone. Travelling into it was -- \f[italic,1]is\f[italic,default] -- a death sentence. The bone-white snow of the Tundra, blown about by the silently rushing winds, is enough to harm you if you breathe it in. During the months of Moonfall, the time when the wind rushes south, we Diamonds close our windows and lock our doors so that the soundless gusts do not take us in our sleep.\n \s[1]Stepping foot there will bleach your hair the colour of the shining moonlight, and the blood of your fingers and lowpaws will slow, making them cold as ice for the rest of your life. \s[3]Then,\w9 if you are lucky,\w9\w5 you will die.\n\n "
	
	"...\w9\w9\s[1]The truth is, the Kyone is the bleakly beating heart of Kosanu. Without it, our culture built of carefulness would not have been born. From a young age, Diamond kits are taught to always take caution in life, lest the Tundra steal their breath away. \s[0]The lessons -- close the doors, layer well, wear a veil so as to avoid the gusts -- help mitigate other sicknesses, frostbite and such... \s[3]but it is a shame that our young are kept safe only by fear. It is not what She would have wanted.\n\n "
	
	"\s[1]Ehm... thank you for listening. \s[0]It is hard to explain how I \f[italic,1]feel\f[italic,default] about the Tundra, \s[3]but... \w9\s[1]it is still nice to share my knowledge about it."
	--
	"\n\n\n\![*]\q[More about Kosanu,OnKosanuBACK]\n\![*]\q[Back to dictionary,OnBACK]\n\![*]\q[Thank you,Cancel]\n"
}

