OnScavva : all
{
	articleopencount++ 
	"\0\s[1]\t\*"
	--
	"Scavva! Oh, what a wonderful place. \s[0]I travel here quite often, for the groceries that Kosani merchants simply don't have... \s[1]as well as to visit for the numerous festivals! \s[0]I may have mentioned Alunocce to you already; it's this quaint little town on the coast, it's my favourite little place in all of Paccevela... \s[1]but that's getting offtopic.\n \w9\s[0]Scavva is the western state of Paccevela, sharing a border with Kosanu's Shui'o Nui Prefecture as well as bordering the Finstrafe Sea. It's the more rural side of the country -- much less hustle and bustle there than in \_a[OnVelanne]Velanne\_a. It's full of farmland, \s[1]as well as wineries, of course. They love their wine over in Paccevela...\n \s[0]A signature dish of Scavva is fish and noodles... \s[1]which, you may be thinking, sounds shockingly similar to the signature dish here in Shui'o Nui... but it actually couldn't taste more like the opposite! \s[0]It impresses me that they figured out how to make something so simple taste entirely different than how we do it over here in Kosanu... \s[1]granted, most of that comes from their choice of fish -- Spadefin, it's called, if you can believe it. \s[0]Well, I'm being unfair; we have Spadefin over here as well, on the northern coast and in the canal separating the two countries, but we never prepare it quite the same. Either way, the way they do it over there is just delicious... \s[1]oh dear, I'm rambling about food again, aren't I?! Alright, alright, I'll wrap it up...\n\n \s[0]"
	
	"Scavva has a few independent temples to Viro here and there, but the main one is located over in \_a[OnVelanne]Velanne\_a -- \s[1]looked after, of course, by my good friend \_a[OnWhoGuardians]Gio\_a\s[0]... still, the smaller temples in Scavva are very quaint! I love to visit the littler ones along the coast, always so beautiful. The architectural style is very unique; a mix of mud-brick and fragrant Olun Cypress, which grows natively along the Canal... \s[1]so very different than our coastal living spaces here in Kosanu! \s[0]Though I suppose that's a given; we would have to dig quite far into the earth to create mud-brick, and  I don't believe we have very durable clay beneath the ground here, like they do over in Paccevela... \s[3]goodness me, I go from food to architecture and I still end up ranting! \s[1] Sorry, sorry. I think that's all there is to know about Scavva... thank you for listening."
	
		if Flag("del") == 1 
		{
			"\n\n \s[1]...Oh, wait, one more fun fact, though I may have mentioned this already... this is where \_a[OnWhoDel]Del Noccione, Ace of Spades\_a, grew up! He lived in that little town I mentioned earlier, Alunocce... \s[0]we talked about it quite a lot, back before he ran off. \s[1]He always had the best restaurant recommendations... ehehe. Okay, \f[italic,1]now\f[italic,default] i'll quit yapping your ear off..."
		}
	--
	"\n\n\n\![*]\q[More about Paccevela,OnPaccevelaBACK]\n\![*]\q[Back to dictionary,OnBACK]\n\![*]\q[Thank you,Cancel]\n"
}
OnVelanne : all
{
	articleopencount++ 
	"\0\s[0]\t\*"
	--
	"\0\s[0]Ah, Velanne... a beautiful place. Being on the eastern half of Paccevela, it's quite the trek for me to visit Velanne, \s[1]but it is well worth it!\n \s[0]The architecture here is stunning, the houses and shops are as diverse in height as the people -- some buildings are so short I hit my head on the ceiling, while others tower above the rest, their chapel-like rooves reaching up to mingle with the clouds. Stained glass is a staple here, whether in tiny forms -- like the front sign of a shop -- or, in the cases such as the Shrine of Paccevela, giant mosaic pieces... \s[1]when the light hits these fragile works of art just right, it's the most beautiful thing you could ever see.\n\n "
	
	"Truth be told, I don't visit Velanne too often; the general population there is of the upper class, something I deal with quite enough in my work as a Guardian... \s[3]they're not as bad as the Facecards, \s[1]but they certainly could learn some manners, especially when dealing with Kosani folk -- \s[3]they don't take too kindly to us...\n \s[0]Anyway! I only really go for the food, and to see \_a[OnWhoGuardians]Gio\_a. As such, I don't have much to say about the place, other than that it's very beautiful...\n My sincerest apologies for the short explanation, %(oomf)!"
	--
	"\n\n\n\![*]\q[More about Paccevela,OnPaccevelaBACK]\n\![*]\q[Back to dictionary,OnBACK]\n\![*]\q[Thank you,Cancel]\n"
}



//lacerta
OnSyk : all
{
	articleopencount++
	
	"\0\s[0]\b[2]\t\*"
	--
	"Ah, Syk! \s[1]It's not the technical capitol of Lacerta -- that would be Iy -- but, culturally, I'd say it has much more sway than the latter. \s[0]It is the most densely populated city in Lacerta... they say, 'if you can make your way through Syk, you can make your way around anywhere in the country.' It's \f[italic,1]that\f[italic,default] crowded!.. \s[3]Hence why I don't visit unless I have to, \s[1]ehehe...\n\n \s[0]Syk is divided into three districts; the South District is the largest, serving as a shopping district. Malls, hotels and casinos are practically stacked on top of each-other... \s[1]oh, and a ton of movies are filmed here, so expect lots of celebrity sightings, too!..\n\n \s[0]The East District is the financial district, full of bustling office-workers... \s[1]and the occasional streetwalker, ha. I suppose it's not too surprising... those working in the financial district would need some 'relief,' too.\n\n \s[0]Last but certainly not least, the North District is the smallest of all, existing mostly as a residential area, but also a bustling red-light district. You couldn't turn a corner here without seeing a strip club...\w9\w9\s[1] or two\w3.\w3.\w3.\w9 \s[3]or\w3 five\w3.\w3.\w3.\w9\n \s[1]Anyways... the North District is a celebrated cornerstone of Lacerta, serving as a testament to Hearts culture's general sexual liberation. As the saying goes, 'Syk creates the culture...' \s[0]though, what it really means is \f[italic,1]North\f[italic,default] Syk creates the culture,\s[1] haha!\n\n \w9\w9\w7Oh, me? Ha! I just go for the food. They make lots of spicy things, and their meats are very heavily seasoned, using a similar technique as in Ani'ani cooking... \s[1]In fact, that's probably the \f[italic,1]only\f[italic,default] attribute we Diamonds share with the Hearts in terms of culture, ehehe...\n\n "
	
	"\s[0]Back when I wrote more journalistic nonfiction as opposed to historical works, I had to go to Syk pretty often. I think my favourite thing about the city was the festivals. \s[1]Words cannot describe how lively and upbeat they are! \s[0]Pretty light shows, amazing food... strange, too. They'll fry just about anything you ask them to.\n ...On one hand, I'd love to go to a Sykae festival again, but on the other, \s[1]I think my guts would appreciate me staying far, far away from those food vendors..."
	--
	"\n\n\n\![*]\q[More about Lacerta,OnLacertaBACK]\n\![*]\q[Back to dictionary,OnBACK]\n\![*]\q[Thank you,Cancel]\n"
}

OnIy
{
	articleopencount++ 
	
	"\0\s[0]\b[2]\t\*"
	--
	"Oh, Iy! Probably my favourite place in Lacerta -- it's near the center of the landmass, bordering Quatangu Loch, so its climate is... er, how should I say this...\w9\w6 well, \s[1]it's not so damn hot. The reason I even visit is simply because it's the \f[italic,1]one place\f[italic,default] in Lacerta where I don't have to \f[italic,1]strip down\f[italic,default] just to survive the weather...\n \s[0]Oh,\w4 right! Uhm,\w6 anyways... Iy is the sort of 'castle town' of Lacerta. The actual Palace is at the northwesternmost tip of Iy, somewhat close to the Academy... I stay far away from it, since the idea of running into \_a[OnWhoMadame]her Majesty\_a or any other nobility makes me nauseous... but, the outer rings are great.\n\n Ah, I should explain... the city is built in 'rings.' Though, they are... not actually circular. They are moreso 'rows,' but I will quit with the pedantics... er, right. The innermost ring -- 'Iy Palacca' -- is the smallest, but most intricate -- this is where the Madame and her family live, and where they hold certain events. It is almost entirely consumed by the Palace itself... however, some 'smaller' mansions border the outskirts of the Palace Gardens.\n\n The Second ring is for Jacks and other rich folk, nothing too interesting there. I once tried to visit it -- I had just gotten away from one of the Madame's feasts, and was trying to find real food. Couldn't find anything worth the money -- you know how snooty folk are, they think they can fill up on a quarter of a reasonable portion... I continued my search until I suddenly got escorted out by the royal police for... er,\w9 well,\w9 the reason they gave was\w9\w6 simply because I am a Pip? And I heard one mention something about me being a Diamond, as well...\w9\w6 suffice to say, I don't visit it much anymore. I would avoid it, if I were you. The food is \f[italic,1]not\f[italic,default] worth the hassle, and their customs are... archaic, to say the least.\n\n Anyway... the Third and Fourth rings are where Iy starts to shine -- when someone says 'Iy,' they are almost definitely talking about these two outermost rings...\n In common Lacertan fashion, there are folks of many walks of life here; not as much of a mixed bag as \_a[OnSyk]Syk\_a, but there are more than a few 'clusters' of other Suits living here. A small section of the city is nicknamed 'Velannicci' -- Pacce for 'little Velanne' -- due to the high population of Spades. 'Clovertown' is a cute little area as well; it's themed entirely around Aidhish tradition, and boasts a large population of Clubs. We Diamonds are spread so thin that we don't have a cute little area for ourselves in Iy... but! I was at least able to find a few restaurants serving authentic Ani'ani cuisine -- something you'd be hard-pressed to find off the island, let alone outside of Kosanu! And let me tell you, it was simply divine...\w9\w4 oh, whoops! I've gotten off-track, haven't I?... Er, right...\n\n Actually... that about wraps it up for Iy, really. If you ever visit, be sure to visit a few Kosani restaurants! You can report back to me if they strike your fancy..."
	--
	"\n\n\n\![*]\q[More about Lacerta,OnLacertaBACK]\n\![*]\q[Back to dictionary,OnBACK]\n\![*]\q[Thank you,Cancel]\n"
}



