OnWhatSuits : all
{
	articleopencount++
	
	"\0\s[0]\t\*"
	--
	"Hum... how to explain, how to explain... the concept of Suits altogether as Cards is quite strange, I am sure. As a small child, I thought we Diamonds were the only ones, until I travelled off the islands for the first time... what a shock! \s[1]Suffice to say, I understand your confusion.\n\n \s[0]I will start with the basics. There are four Suits; Diamonds, Spades, Clubs, and Hearts. \_a[OnWhatCard]We are altogether known as 'Cards,'\_a and we each inhabit a \_a[OnPlacesFAQ]Quadrant\_a on the landmass.\n We Diamonds are native, of course, to \_a[OnKosanuFAQ]Kosanu\_a; Spades, to \_a[OnPaccevelaFAQ]Paccevela\_a; Clubs reside in "
	
		//"\_a[OnAidhmooreFAQ]Aidhmoore\_a,"
		"\f[color,disable]Aidhmoore\f[color,default],"

	" and finally, Hearts in \_a[OnLacertaFAQ]Lacerta\_a.\n\n " // CHANGE THIS WHEN YOU ADD AIDHMOORE DAMMIT!!!
	
	"\s[1]I am a Diamond, and so I will start by telling you about my own Suit! \s[0]We Diamonds are often lanky, fuzzy folk\s[1]... our big, fluffy tails and ears are what often gives us away, as well as the prehensile little antennae on our heads\s[0]. Oh, right... I guess we generally have more eyes than the other Suits, too... \s[1]I always forget that! When I travel, I tend to wonder how everyone else sees, having only two or three... \s[0]ah, \s[3]I hope that isn't insensitive! \s[1]Ahem...\n We're generally more suited for colder environments, having hailed from a land of snow and ice. \s[0]Our Suit is represented, of course, by a four-pointed diamond shape, but we also tend to use the four-pointed star as a secondary symbol. \s[1]Much more artsy... ehehe. \s[0]The First Ace of Diamonds is \_a[OnWhoAlonaia]Alonai'a\_a -- we Diamonds hold the Firsts in much higher regard than the others tend to... \s[1]ehm, we have our reasons for doing so, but... that's irrelevant, for now. "
	
	
		"\w9\w9\n\n\f[color,disable]\f[sup,1]\![quicksection,1]click anywhere to continue\n\q[click here to quit reading the article,OnBACK]\![quicksection,0]\f[sup,0]\f[color,default]\x \s[0]\b[2]"
	
	
	"\s[0]Moving along... Spades, the Suit of Paccevela! Spades are often characterized by the richly coloured markings on their skin. The most common colours you will see is a primary cream or tan, fading to a beautiful jet black or dark blue colour along their limbs, almost like gloves or long socks... \s[1]very, very pretty! \w4\s[0]They also tend to have very large horns -- one such example is my good friend Gio, whose twisted horns wrap all the way 'round the back of his head, poking up around his face. \s[3]With his beard and thick hair, I often imagine him as a fluffy little Sunnai... \s[3]but, he didn't seem to appreciate my comparison of his head to my neighbor's livestock, so... \s[1] \w8ehehe.\n \s[0]Their Suit is represented by a peculiar symbol, which looks a bit like an upside down heart with a trunk. Their First Ace is Viro, who many of its citizens don't care much for or know of... however, as you get close to the coast and further from the Facecards' iron grip, you may start to see more shrines and temples dedicated to Viro. \s[1]Gio, the Guardian of the Shrine of Paccevela, is the first of his lineage to truly spread the word that Viro was not as barbaric as the Facecards make him seem... and truly, what an accomplishment on his part! \s[0]I digress, however; I'm getting offtopic, rambling about my dear friend. Onto the other teachings, hm? "
	
		"\w9\w9\n\n\f[color,disable]\f[sup,1]\![quicksection,1]click anywhere to continue\n\q[click here to quit reading the article,OnBACK]\![quicksection,0]\f[sup,0]\f[color,default]\x \s[0]\b[2]"
	
	
	"Clubs, the suit of Aidhmoore, were also originally islanders -- as they are directly to the south of Kosanu, they were among the first to ever meet our own Suit, and we have been very close ever since. They, too, have big fluffy ears -- yet also, stubby little tails, very cute. They are shorter and much more stout than we Diamonds -- being tall even for my Suit, I tend to tower over them... \s[3]though, as their Suit is known for being very dense and muscular, I am sure many of them could take me down in seconds...\s[1] ehehe!\n \s[0]\w2The horns on their head often don't grow very much... \s[1]but, ehm, despite their size, they sure do hurt when a Club headbutts you! \s[3]I'll never forget the day Claris rammed her head into my side, as is a traditional friendly Aidhish greeting... \s[1]she had to carry me to a cot, I couldn't trust myself to walk!\n \s[0]Anyway... Clubs are represented by a little clover symbol, be it three-leafed or four. Their First Ace is Nore, who many on the mainland have forgotten... \s[1]however, their memory is alive and well on the Lamnthine Islands, where the Shrine of Aidhmoore resides. "
	
		"\w9\w9\n\n\f[color,disable]\f[sup,1]\![quicksection,1]click anywhere to continue\n\q[click here to quit reading the article,OnBACK]\![quicksection,0]\f[sup,0]\f[color,default]\x \s[0]\b[2]"
	
	"Lastly, the Lacertan Hearts, by far the most plentiful on the landmass. There is so much diversity in their appearance that it's hard to describe them, but they all have long tails -- some bare, some slightly fuzzy... most of them have horns which look a bit like the mandibles of certain insects, though they aren't prehensile like Diamonds' antennae are. Each -- \s[3]\w3well,\w8 \s[1]\f[italic,1]most\f[italic,default] Hearts have what is known as a "

		//"\_a[OnWhatSykaeParasites]Sykae Parasite\_a,"
		"\f[color,disable]Sykae Parasite\f[color,default]," // CHANGE WHEN YOU ADD SYKAE PARASITES

	" \s[0]a secondary entity within some part of the host's body, usually a limb or eye or whatnot. Usually, they are silent and only speak... \s[3]ehm, I assume through brainwaves or somesuch, \s[1]with their host and no one else; others may speak using the mouth of their host, usually if that parasite is located near the face in some way; others still may 'speak' by emitting vibrations in the air using their host's flow. Very interesting!\n The First Ace of Hearts is Lairu. There is... \s[3]not much reverence held for them. Inola, the Guardian of the Shrine of Lacerta, gets the least amount of visitors of any shrine, despite the large population surrounding her temple. She... loves people, it's a shame she doesn't get to speak to like-minded folk more often. \s[1]\n Ehm... sorry, got offtrack. Right... \s[0]Hearts are represented by, well, a little love-heart. \s[1]Never would have guessed, would you? Ehehe...\n\n "
	
	"\s[0]I think that about sums it up, though. I hope my explanations suffice! \s[1]Of course, the best way to learn about the Suits is to immerse yourself in their culture, travel 'round the Quadrants, meet folks... \s[0]but, I understand if you'd rather learn some pointers before doing all of that. \s[1]It warms my heart that you would ask \f[italic,1]me\f[italic,default] to help you learn, %(oomf)."
	--
	"\n\n\n\![*]\q[More miscellaneous information,OnStuffBACK]\n\![*]\q[Back to dictionary,OnBACK]\n\![*]\q[Thank you,Cancel]\n"
	
	if Flag("suits article read") == 0; MiscFlags ,= "suits article read"
}

OnWhatFlow : all
{
	articleopencount++
	
	"\0\s[0]\t\*"
	--
	"Oh! Right, I forgot they don't teach this stuff in schools anymore..."
	{
		if talkcount < 5 || articleopencount < 3; " allow me to explain."
		else; " I apologize, I've probably prattled on about flow and rank without thinking to explain them!"
	}
	"\n\n 'Flow' is the ability to harness the energy in your body, and use it to affect the world around you. It has a physical presence in your body, and can be seen by a special type of people, aptly named 'Seers...' more on them in a moment.\n\n Your 'rank' is a title given to you by a Seer at a certain age -- that age depends on which Quadrant you're in, how far away you are from the mainland, if your family is nobility... et cetera.\n A Seer will 'read' the flow of energy within your body, and assign you a number. Now, that specific number is secret -- only the government knows it -- but they will tell you whether you are a Pip or a Jack... or, well, there's Aces, too, but... \s[1]ehm, that's complicated. We will get to them another time. There's only four every hundred or so years, so they're not too important to explain right now...\n\n \s[0]Anyways!.. Pips are 'normal folk,' like you and I. We have very little flow, and many of us can barely use spells -- if at all. For us, the names 'rank' and 'flow' are somewhat interchangeable, and many won't get on your case if you accidentally say one when you meant the other.\n A Jack, on the other hand, is \f[height,-1]\w2almost\w2\f[height,default] any Card that has high flow. Freshly-read Jacks, even if they are the poorest of the poor, get sort of... forced into nobility. The civilian population is, in a way, artificially tampered with to keep the average flow low... \s[3]this is done to keep the physically stronger Cards in power, and anyone weak is left to fend for themselves. It is... a cruel system.\n\n \s[1]Right... um, Facecards are a Rank, \s[0]but being a Facecard is not really based on flow. Being a 'Facecard' simply means you are part of one of the four royal families. Due to having good genetics \f[height,-2]\w3\s[3]...as well as, up until recently, quite a bit of 'keeping it in the family,' in the case of Hearts' and Spades' royal families,\w2\s[0]\f[height,default] the Facecards \f[italic,1]do\f[italic,default] tend to have very high flow, but... \s[1]it's not required. It's simply a title. As much as they don't want to admit it, royals are simply people, just like us.\n\n \s[0]"

	"To make it short... Flow is innate, and Rank is governmental. \n\s[1]The way I see it, neither matter at all. We are all people, and we are all good at different things. The fire burning within you is bright, no matter the strength of the kindling. \n \s[0]...I hope my explanation suffices, %(oomf)."
	-- 
	"\n\n\n\![*]\q[More miscellaneous information,OnStuffBACK]\n\![*]\q[Back to dictionary,OnBACK]\n\![*]\q[Thank you,Cancel]\n"
	
	if Flag("flow article read") == 0; MiscFlags ,= "flow article read"
}

