OnWhoGuardians; { OnWhatGuardianship } //since i keep fucking typing it like that
OnWhatGuardianship : all
{
	articleopencount++
	
	"\0\s[0]\b2\t\*"
	--
	"\0\s[1]I realize I should explain Guardianship... \s[0]I'd say it's a bit of a niche and novel concept, but really, the Guardians have been around just as long as the Aces. It's just that we are, well... less powerful, less important. \s[1]I like it that way, really...\n \s[0]The first Guardians were each granted divinity by their respective First Ace. This divinity simply grants us the ability to control the energy of the temples we take care of, as well as any other shrines within that suit's 'jurisdiction,' so to speak. It can also grant you a longer lifespan, if you're lucky! Biologically speaking, it is a physical 'piece' of the First's flow, implanted within us and acting as a sort of 'key' for the shrines. Though... flow is -- in its natural state -- invisible, so this may seem like a bit of a silly explanation. I simply view it as a blessing; easier to explain that way...\n\n "
	"Guardianship -- and that divinity along with it -- is passed down when the current Guardian passes away. Furthermore, each Guardian keeps pupils, training them so that, when the time comes, their students may take on a set of ceremonial trials and claim Guardianship.\n This ceremonial training can take anywhere from one to five years, and it can be\w2.\w2.\w2. \w9\s[1]pretty\w3 harrowing. \s[0]The intensity varies based on the suit, but... my goodness! \s[1]The Paccevele Shrine's training is... almost violent! Lacertan training is also very dangerous, as it involves learning to channel the energy of the Black Desert. \s[3]It is... sometimes a wonder to me that the students make it out at all. \s[1]Anyways...\w9 \s[1]questions?\n\n "
	"...Oh? When did \f[italic,1]I\f[italic,default] go through training?.. \s[1]Ehm\w2.\w2.\w2. \w9long ago! \s[0]Before they started keeping track, ahaha... \s[3]er, \w9anyways, \s[1]I should tell you of the others...\n\n \s[0]"
	
		"\w9\w9\n\n\f[color,disable]\f[sup,1]\![quicksection,1]click anywhere to continue\n\q[click here to quit reading the article,OnBACK]\![quicksection,0]\f[sup,0]\f[color,default]\x \s[0]\b[2]"
	
	"Claris Dorsch is the Guardian of the Shrine of Aidhmoore, or simply the 'Shrine of Clubs.' The Shrine is located on the island of Lamnthe,\s[1] and she keeps it very tidy and nice! \s[0]She has been the Guardian for around 20 years now. I am good friends with all of the Guardians, \s[1]but it is easiest to visit Claris, so we see eachother a lot! \s[0]Because of an injury she sustained when she was very young, I help out around the shrine quite a bit during Newbloom -- its busiest season... we have a lot of time to chat during then. "
	
		"\w9\w9\n\n\f[color,disable]\f[sup,1]\![quicksection,1]click anywhere to continue\n\q[click here to quit reading the article,OnBACK]\![quicksection,0]\f[sup,0]\f[color,default]\x \s[0]\b[2]"
	
	"Gio Lansione is the Guardian of Paccevela, or Spades. The Shrine is located in \_a[OnVelanne]Velanne Arona\_a"
		--
		if Flag("paccevela town grammar") == 1; ", a very pretty town...\n "
		else; " \f[height,-2]...er, that's a town in Velanne; in Paccevela, the state name goes before the town name. Anyways... \f[height,default]\n "
		--
	"\s[1]Sir Lansione and I are very good friends, as well! We bond, of course, over our shared knowledge of Viro and Alonai'a... \s[0]though, Gio is more of a fighter than a scholar. \s[1]He himself is surprised he claimed Guardianship over his peers! \s[0]Though I suppose it makes sense, seeing as the Paccevele ceremonial training is so physically demanding. \s[3]A bookworm like myself could never make it through the spars the students must complete...\w6\s[1] haha!\n \w9\s[0]Gio and I don't visit often, despite our proximity. We prefer to write eachother letters... in reality, \s[1]I think he just dislikes marching through the sickening cold to come see me, ha! \s[0]I don't blame him; I avoid travelling to Velanne for... \w9\s[3]other\w9 reasons. We\w9 will just say that the general population of the state is\w2.\w2.\w2. not too keen on Diamonds being there. \w9\w9\s[0]Gio is not like that, though! \w9\s[1]He is a very kind man. \s[0]"
	
		"\w9\w9\n\n\f[color,disable]\f[sup,1]\![quicksection,1]click anywhere to continue\n\q[click here to quit reading the article,OnBACK]\![quicksection,0]\f[sup,0]\f[color,default]\x \s[0]\b[2]"
	
	"Last but not least... Inola Reed is the Guardian of the Shrine of Lacerta, or Hearts. The Shrine is located in Chiluno, a small town with close proximity to the Black Desert. \f[italic,1]Despite\f[italic,default] its proximity to the Desert, the Shrine Guardian works with the temple's energy to keep Chiluno a calm and pleasant place to live -- \s[1]not an easy feat! \w9\s[0]Inola, though young, has probably the most difficult job out of all of us -- \s[3]along with perhaps myself. \s[0]Where I must stave off the energy-sapping characteristics of the Kyone, \s[1]Inola must work with the hazardous energy spikes of the Desert; \s[3]something that can kill someone without the divinity we Guardians possess. \s[1]She is very brave to take on this job.\n\n "
	
	"\w9\w9...Thank you for letting me tell you about my job, and my friends! I care about all of this very deeply. Any questions you may have are mine to answer! \w9"
	--
	"\n\n\n\![*]\q[More miscellaneous information,OnStuffBACK]\n\![*]\q[Back to dictionary,OnBACK]\n\![*]\q[Thank you,Cancel]\n"
	
	if Flag("claris") == 0; MiscFlags ,= "claris"
	if Flag("inola") == 0; MiscFlags ,= "inola"
	if Flag("gio") == 0; MiscFlags ,= "gio"
	
	if Flag("paccevela town grammar") == 0; MiscFlags ,= "paccevela town grammar"

}

